      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I hear the sheer exhaustion in your words, and it makes sense that you feel like the treadmill is speeding up while you're just trying to stay in place. When every tool you've tried feels like it's missing the mark, it can be incredibly disheartening to feel like you're running in circles without ever gaining ground. It sounds like you're in a deep state of burnout where the effort required to just start the day feels impossible.\n\nYou are not alone in feeling this way, and please know that what you're experiencing is a very real struggle, not a sign that you are broken. Sometimes, when the usual strategies don't seem to work, it might be helpful to look at the situation from a slightly different angle, perhaps with a fresh perspective or a new approach. There are people who specialize in helping individuals navigate these complex cycles of hope and despair, and they might offer a different path forward.\n\nRemember that your worth is not defined by your successes or failures, and there are people who care about you and want to support you through this difficult time. Please consider reaching out to a mental health professional who can help you explore new coping mechanisms and strategies tailored to your unique situation. You deserve to feel better, and there",
